    <div class="bg-off-white border-l-3 border-l-teal rounded-lg p-6 mb-12">
      <p class="text-[15px] text-teal font-medium leading-relaxed m-0"><strong>Key insight:</strong> The platform you choose sets a ceiling on your AI visibility. A beautifully designed Wix site will always struggle compared to a properly built WordPress or Astro site, because the underlying code determines what AI can read. We rebuilt our own site from Lovable to Astro after 244 indexed pages dropped to 47 overnight.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">1. Astro</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Astro is a static site generator that produces pure HTML with zero JavaScript by default. Every page is pre-rendered at build time, meaning AI crawlers receive the full content instantly with no client-side processing required. This is the platform Rank4AI runs on, and we chose it specifically because AI readability was our top priority.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Zero JavaScript output by default. AI crawlers read every word.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Fastest possible page load speeds. Perfect Lighthouse scores are standard.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Clean semantic HTML structure with no framework bloat.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Full control over schema markup, meta tags and crawl directives.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">No plugins to slow things down or block crawlers.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Requires developer knowledge. Not a drag-and-drop builder.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">No built-in CMS. Content is managed in code files or via a headless CMS.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Smaller ecosystem than WordPress or React-based frameworks.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-teal font-medium"><strong>AI verdict:</strong> The best platform for AI search visibility if you have development resources.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">2. Next.js (with static export)</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Next.js is a React framework that can generate static HTML pages at build time. When configured for static export, it produces crawlable HTML similar to Astro. The key distinction is that Next.js ships a JavaScript runtime alongside the HTML, which adds weight but enables interactive features.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Static export produces server-rendered HTML that AI crawlers can read.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Massive developer community and ecosystem.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Flexible rendering modes: static, server-side, or hybrid.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Excellent TypeScript support and modern tooling.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Ships JavaScript runtime even for static pages, adding page weight.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Easy to accidentally use client-side rendering, which AI crawlers cannot process.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Requires developer expertise. Not suitable for non-technical users.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-teal font-medium"><strong>AI verdict:</strong> Excellent for AI visibility when using static export, but requires careful configuration to avoid client-rendering pitfalls.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">3. WordPress (properly configured)</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">WordPress powers over 40% of all websites, and with the right configuration it can produce AI-readable output. The critical word is "properly configured." Out-of-the-box WordPress with a bloated theme and 30 plugins will score poorly. A lean WordPress install with a lightweight theme, proper caching and schema plugins can compete with purpose-built solutions.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Huge plugin ecosystem for SEO, schema and performance.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Non-technical users can manage content after initial setup.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Strong community support and documentation.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Server-rendered HTML by default.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Plugin bloat is common and degrades AI readability.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Security plugins often block AI crawlers by default.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Themes generate messy, nested HTML with poor semantic structure.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Constant updates risk breaking optimisations.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-teal font-medium"><strong>AI verdict:</strong> A strong choice when properly configured, but requires ongoing maintenance to keep AI readability high.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">4. Webflow</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Webflow generates relatively clean HTML and gives designers visual control without writing code. It sits in a good middle ground: better output quality than most drag-and-drop builders, with a gentler learning curve than code-first tools. AI crawlers can generally read Webflow sites, though the HTML is not as clean as Astro or properly configured WordPress.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Visual builder with relatively clean HTML output.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Built-in CMS and hosting. No plugins to manage.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Good performance out of the box.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Custom code embed support for schema markup.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">HTML includes Webflow-specific classes and wrappers that add noise.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Limited control over robots.txt and crawl directives.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Schema markup requires manual code embeds rather than native support.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-teal font-medium"><strong>AI verdict:</strong> A solid choice for design-led businesses. Not perfect for AI, but significantly better than Wix or Squarespace.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">5. Shopify</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Shopify has invested heavily in performance and SEO over the past two years. Product pages generate structured data automatically, and the platform handles server-side rendering well. For ecommerce businesses, Shopify is the strongest option for AI visibility because it produces product schema that AI search engines understand natively.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Built-in product schema markup on all product pages.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Fast CDN-backed hosting included.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Server-rendered HTML for product and collection pages.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Large app ecosystem for additional SEO enhancements.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Blog functionality is basic and produces limited structured data.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">URL structure is rigid (forced /products/, /collections/ paths).</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Apps can add JavaScript bloat similar to WordPress plugins.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-teal font-medium"><strong>AI verdict:</strong> The best ecommerce platform for AI search. Product schema is handled well, but content pages need work.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">6. Squarespace</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Squarespace produces server-rendered HTML, which is better than fully client-rendered alternatives. However, the HTML structure includes significant platform-specific markup, deeply nested divs, and limited control over technical SEO elements. AI crawlers can read the content but often struggle to identify what is important within the noise.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Server-rendered HTML. Content is visible to crawlers.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Beautiful templates that require minimal design skill.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Built-in SSL, hosting and basic SEO settings.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">No native schema markup support. Requires code injection.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Limited control over robots.txt and AI crawler directives.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">HTML structure is bloated with platform-specific wrappers.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Cannot add llms.txt or ai-sitemap.txt files.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-teal font-medium"><strong>AI verdict:</strong> Acceptable for small businesses, but the ceiling on AI visibility is low. You will always be outranked by competitors on better platforms.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">7. Wix</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Wix has improved significantly since its early days, but it still relies heavily on JavaScript for rendering. While Wix now offers server-side rendering for some content, many page elements are still loaded client-side. AI crawlers that do not execute JavaScript will miss substantial portions of your content.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Extremely easy to use. No technical knowledge required.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Server-side rendering now available for core content.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Built-in SEO tools are improving.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Heavy JavaScript dependency for many page elements.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Slow page load speeds compared to static alternatives.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Limited control over HTML output and page structure.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Cannot customise robots.txt for AI crawlers or add llms.txt.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-teal font-medium"><strong>AI verdict:</strong> Easy to use but fundamentally limited for AI search. Fine for a personal site, risky for a business that needs AI visibility.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">8. Lovable / Bolt / v0</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">AI-powered website builders like Lovable, Bolt and v0 produce visually impressive sites in minutes. The problem is that they generate React single-page applications where all content is rendered via JavaScript. AI crawlers like GPTBot and PerplexityBot cannot execute JavaScript, so they see an empty page. The site looks great to humans but is invisible to AI.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Fastest way to go from idea to working prototype.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">No coding knowledge needed at all.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Modern, attractive designs by default.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">JavaScript-only rendering. AI crawlers see little to no content.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">No schema markup, no robots.txt control, no llms.txt support.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Poor SEO fundamentals. Missing meta tags, canonical URLs and sitemaps.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Not designed for production use or long-term maintenance.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-teal font-medium"><strong>AI verdict:</strong> Useful for prototyping but not suitable for any business that wants to be found in AI search results.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">9. Framer</h2>
    <div class="bg-white border border-border rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Framer generates fast, visually polished websites with decent performance. It uses server-side rendering for initial page loads, which means AI crawlers can access the content. However, Framer's SEO capabilities are limited. There is no native schema support, restricted robots.txt control, and the HTML output includes framework-specific code that adds noise for AI parsers.</p>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Strengths:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Fast page loads and smooth animations.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Server-side rendering makes content visible to crawlers.</li>
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">Excellent design tools for portfolios and landing pages.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-3"><strong>Weaknesses:</strong></p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-5 space-y-2">
        <li class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">No native schema markup support.</li>
