      <details class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-heading cursor-pointer">Why is Astro ranked first?</summary>
        <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mt-3">Astro generates pure static HTML with zero JavaScript by default. This means AI crawlers can read every word on every page instantly. There is no client-side rendering to interfere.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-heading cursor-pointer">Is WordPress good for AI search?</summary>
        <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mt-3">Yes, when properly configured. WordPress with the right theme, caching plugin and schema plugin produces clean, crawlable HTML. The risk is plugins that add bloat or security tools that block AI crawlers.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-heading cursor-pointer">Why do Lovable and Bolt score so low?</summary>
        <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mt-3">They produce JavaScript-heavy single-page applications. AI crawlers like GPTBot and PerplexityBot cannot execute JavaScript, so they see little to no content. The sites look great to humans but are invisible to AI.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="border border-border rounded-lg p-5">
        <summary class="font-semibold text-heading cursor-pointer">Should I rebuild my website for AI search?</summary>
        <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mt-3">Only if your current platform fundamentally cannot produce AI-readable output. If you are on WordPress, Webflow or Shopify, optimising your existing site is usually more cost-effective than rebuilding.</p>
